{"metadata":{"symbolKind":"class","fragments":[{"text":"MLNPolyline","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"MLNPolyline","externalID":"c:objc(cs)MLNPolyline","role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Class","modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNPolyline"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre"]]},"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["occ"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"@interface"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNPolyline"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:objc(cs)MLNMultiPoint","text":"MLNMultiPoint","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPoint"}],"platforms":["iOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can add polyline shapes to the map by adding them to an "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeSource"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"object. Configure the appearance of an "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeSource"},{"type":"text","text":"’s or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNVectorTileSource"},{"type":"text","text":"’s polylines collectively using an "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNLineStyleLayer"},{"type":"text","text":" or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNSymbolStyleLayer"},{"type":"text","text":" object. To access a polyline’s attributes, use an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolylineFeature"},{"type":"text","text":" object."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Alternatively, you can add a polyline overlay directly to a map view using the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView\/addAnnotation:","type":"reference"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView\/addOverlay:","type":"reference"},{"text":" methods. Configure","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a polyline overlay’s appearance using","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapViewDelegate\/mapView:strokeColorForShapeAnnotation:","type":"reference"},{"text":" and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapViewDelegate\/mapView:lineWidthForPolylineAnnotation:","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The vertices are automatically connected in the order in which you provide"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"them. The first and last vertices are not connected to each other, but you can"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"specify the same "},{"code":"CLLocationCoordinate2D","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" as the first and last vertices in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"order to close the polyline. To fill the space within the shape, use an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object. To group multiple polylines together in one shape, use an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolyline","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeCollection","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To make the polyline go across the antimeridian or international date line,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"specify some longitudes less than −180 degrees or greater than 180 degrees.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"For example, a polyline that stretches from Tokyo to San Francisco would have","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"coordinates of (35.68476, -220.24257) and (37.78428, -122.41310).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let coordinates = [","    CLLocationCoordinate2D(latitude: 35.68476, longitude: -220.24257),","    CLLocationCoordinate2D(latitude: 37.78428, longitude: -122.41310)","]","let polyline = MLNPolyline(coordinates: coordinates, count: UInt(coordinates.count))"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A polyline is known as a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"LineString","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"geometry in GeoJSON.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":4,"anchor":"Related-examples","text":"Related examples","type":"heading"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/LineOnUserTap","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/AnimatedLineExample","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}]}],"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentatio